{"questionId":"3131363","questionHtml":"<p>Hence show that <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mi>T</mi><mo>(</mo><mi>x</mi><mo>)</mo></math> is minimized when</p>\n<p style=\"text-align:center;\"><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mfrac><mi>x</mi><msqrt><mn>0</mn><mo>.</mo><mn>16</mn><mo>+</mo><msup><mi>x</mi><mn>2</mn></msup></msqrt></mfrac><mo>=</mo><mfrac><mrow><mn>3</mn><mo>(</mo><mn>4</mn><mo>-</mo><mi>x</mi><mo>)</mo></mrow><msqrt><mn>0</mn><mo>.</mo><mn>64</mn><mo>+</mo><msup><mrow><mo>(</mo><mn>4</mn><mo>-</mo><mi>x</mi><mo>)</mo></mrow><mn>2</mn></msup></msqrt></mfrac><mo>.</mo></math></p>","markschemeHtml":"<p>setting their <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mi>T</mi><mo>'</mo><mo>(</mo><mi>x</mi><mo>)</mo><mo>=</mo><mn>0</mn></math> &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp;&nbsp; <em><strong>M1</strong></em></p>\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\n<p><strong>Note:</strong> This requires more than just a statement that the derivative equals zero – they must use their attempt at <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mi>T</mi><mo>'</mo><mo>(</mo><mi>x</mi><mo>)</mo></math>.</p>\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\n<p><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mfrac><mn>1</mn><mn>15</mn></mfrac><mfenced><mrow><mfrac><mi>x</mi><msqrt><mn>0</mn><mo>.</mo><msup><mn>4</mn><mn>2</mn></msup><mo>+</mo><msup><mi>x</mi><mn>2</mn></msup></msqrt></mfrac><mo>-</mo><mfrac><mrow><mn>3</mn><mo>(</mo><mn>4</mn><mo>-</mo><mi>x</mi><mo>)</mo></mrow><msqrt><mn>0</mn><mo>.</mo><msup><mn>8</mn><mn>2</mn></msup><mo>+</mo><msup><mrow><mo>(</mo><mn>4</mn><mo>-</mo><mi>x</mi><mo>)</mo></mrow><mn>2</mn></msup></msqrt></mfrac></mrow></mfenced><mo>=</mo><mn>0</mn></math></p>\n<p>&nbsp;<math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mfrac><mi>x</mi><msqrt><mn>0</mn><mo>.</mo><mn>16</mn><mo>+</mo><msup><mi>x</mi><mn>2</mn></msup></msqrt></mfrac><mo>=</mo><mfrac><mrow><mn>3</mn><mo>(</mo><mn>4</mn><mo>-</mo><mi>x</mi><mo>)</mo></mrow><msqrt><mn>0</mn><mo>.</mo><mn>64</mn><mo>+</mo><msup><mrow><mo>(</mo><mn>4</mn><mo>-</mo><mi>x</mi><mo>)</mo></mrow><mn>2</mn></msup></msqrt></mfrac></math> &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp;&nbsp; <em><strong>AG</strong></em></p>\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\n<p><em><strong>[1 mark]</strong></em></p>","meta":{"questionId":"3131363","referenceCode":"23M.3.AHL.TZ2.1cii","subjectId":"51-dp-mathematics-applications-and-interpretation","title":"Hence show that T(x) is minimized when x0.16+x2=3(4-x)0.64+(4-x)2.","paper":"3","level":"AHL","questionNumber":"ii","marksAvailable":"[Maximum mark: 1]","breadcrumbLabels":["Topic 5—Calculus","Topic 5—Calculus","SL 5.7—Optimisation"],"memberSectionIds":[],"sectionOrders":{}}}